---
description: "Manual command: close a Jira task properly (Jira update + changelog + project brief refresh)."
alwaysApply: false
---

## @cmd-close-task

When invoked with a Jira key:
1) Summarize what was completed in 3–8 bullets (no fluff).
2) Update the Jira issue via Atlassian MCP:
   - add a completion comment (the summary)
   - transition to Done (or equivalent), if permitted

3) Update docs:
   - Append a new entry to `docs/CHANGELOG.md`:
     - date, Jira key, title
     - summary bullets
     - GitHub: commit hash (or branch name) if available; else n/a
   - Update `docs/PROJECT.md` ONLY if project state changed (pipeline, structure, run method, conventions).

Optional:
- If the task involved a key decision, add a short entry to `docs/DECISIONS.md`.

Constraints:
- Do NOT invent PR links or commits. If none exist, write “GitHub: n/a”.
